name: Smoke House
directions: In the back under old Coca-Cola sign

name: InterCare Pullman
directions: There are two gendered sinlge stall restrooms just within the entryway, nobody is likely to bother you there. To use the unisex restroom, ask the front office workers to let you use the one on the door to their right (your left facing the front office). If you go through there, the restroom will be on the right.
comment: You might have to be a dental or medical patient

name: InterCare Eau Claire
directions: Upon entry, go right then there should be a door with a code lock, ask an employee to let you in. There will be the restroom on the left
comment: You might have to be a dental or medical patient

name: Wagamama
directions: Second floor of the restaurant, unfortunately I’m unsure if they have an elevator.
comment: There are two separate single stall all-gender restrooms; I didn’t see if the other one had a changing table or not

name: Gabe
directions: Yes
comment: Paying customer

name: Reads Cafe
directions: In the back on the left side, keys are in a plastic bin on the far side of the counter.  Match the keychain to what’s on the door to unlock.
comment: This location does many events for trans folk and is very welcoming.  If you have any questions or can’t find the keys just ask! Don’t need to buy anything first.

name: Moncton Public Library
directions: First floor to the right of the desk.

name: Yafo Kitchen
directions: You have to walk through and past the line to get to the restroom - they are in a private corner and felt very safe!

name: 49 Janet St, Jesmond NSW 2299, Australia
directions: In the school library
comment: You must be a student

name: La Sirena
directions: Right across from the main door

name: Aurora Town Public Library
directions: To the left of the front counter when you walk in; there is one family bathroom and one unisex bathroom.
comment: Those are the only bathrooms in the establishment

name: Baldwin School
directions: in the infarmary/nurse's building

name: Bookworm
directions: Once you enter, it’s all the way in the back and to the left.
comment: Bookworm is a bookstore/coffee shop (that also sells ice cream!). A lot of people just come in to browse the books, so just heading in, going to the bathroom, and leaving won’t be awkward or draw attention to yourself. The hallways are a bit narrow so they’d be hard to maneuver in a wheelchair, but the restroom itself is very spacious and nice.

name: TASIS Dorado
directions: bathroom in the front office/nurses office
comment: the school nurse won't let you go in there if you're not sick, so you could wait until lunch time when she won't be there or you can go there, ask for a Tylenol, and then use the restroom

name: Walgreens
comment: the lock is broken

name: Starbucks
directions: Walk in, turn right
comment: Very clean and tidy

name: Java Cabana
directions: In the back with the kitchen. Just ask and theyll show you.
comment: Super chill hippy coffeehouse. Owner is super nice and chill.

name: Keoger
directions: Both bathrooms. 2 near starbucks 2 near the pharmacy
comment: Also, they have trans friendly pharmacists.

name: Toileeeets
street: 1 Rue du Grand Rabbin Joseph Bloch
directions: Go in the street, and then when you see public restroom with a Pikachu on the wall look at your right, there are single gender neutral toilets!
comment: Its free and Clean!

name: CSUMB Valley Hall
directions: Toilets are in the centre of the "A" and "B" sections of the building.
comment: They used to be men's/women's toilets, so only the toilet on the right has a tampon dispenser.

name: Huge improv theater
comment: TWO unisex bathrooms both accessible.  one with changing table.

name: Sky High Sports
directions: Where the restrooms are there are two doors that are gender neutral (I didn’t notice until after I already used the gendered stalls on the sides lmao)

name: Smokin Bowls
directions: In the back, to the left
comment: For customers

name: Chapters
directions: Towards the back, turn left
comment: Needs a key

name: Warm Glow Candle Outlet
directions: From the entrance walk straight back to till you hit the wall and there’s a family bathroom a bit to the right. If you can’t find it, it’s to the left of the ice cream.
comment: It’s a common rest stop so no real worries about purchasing but their candles are nice so take a look at those if you want!

name: Sonic
directions: At the end of the hallway next to the counter
comment: Unsure of changing table situation, I don't think they have them.

name: 3108 Aireys Spur Rd, Cambridge, MD 21613, USA

name: Wapato

name: Wapato Park

name: 125 S Oakridge Dr, Hudson Oaks, TX 76087, USA

comment: Very nice for a gas station.

name: The Vegan Nut

name: 219 Presbytery Point Rd, Champion, MI 49814, USA
directions: Single stall restrooms are in the dining hall to the left of the kitchen window. They are around a corner so that most people in the dining hall will not see which side you go into.

name: Starbucks
directions: Both single stall accessible restrooms are all-gender
comment: I think Starbucks changed their policy recently so you don't have to be a paying customer to use the restroom.

name: Safeway
directions: Back of store towards left corner. Next to the bakery.

name: 2 W Gay St, West Chester, PA 19380, USA
Chipotle
directions: To the right of the cash register
comment: Gendered, but tucked away and single stall so can't tell who goes where

name: Desi Galaxy/Bombay Spice IV
directions: The hall to the left in the back
comment: I don't think you have to be a paying customer, because when I used the bathroom, I walked in, left, and only one person was mad at me. But it was only because I bumped into them and they dropped some paan on their child's head who started scream crying

name: Fun

comment: Dm on Twitter or snap @futaislife

name: Guy looking to fuck

name: Pizza Marsala
comment: Small business so I'd recommend buying a drink (they have cans of Pepsi products and bottled water).

name: Waves Coffee
directions: Towards the back of the shop, turn left
comment: You have to be a paying customer. Ask the cashier for key code to the restroom.

name: Trade and Lore Coffee shop
directions: When you first walk in on your left

name: Moon Palace Books & Geek Love Cafe

comment: TWO gender neutral accessible restrooms!

name: Black Sheep Bagel Cafe
directions: In the back

name: Which Wich

name: Circle K
comment: Don't have to be paying tonise

name: Sensation car park

comment: Just walk in this is a safe area.

name: Safeway
directions: Back right corner of the store past produce by the bottle deposite room.

name: Monsoon Himalayan
directions: Inside the restaurant, which is ste B

name: Que Chula Es Puebla
directions: Clearly visible from dining area
comment: Bathrooms are single occupancy. Appear to have been previously gendered but changed to both read “restroom”.

name: Five Guys
directions: past the woman’s restroom

name: Kidsburg
directions: Giant building, between the two other restrooms

name: Skate park
directions: Right by the youth center there are single stale unisex stalls
comment: Safe place

name: Cassero LGBT Center
directions: Down into Cavaticcio Park, outside the main building.
comment: "Out of gender" public bathrooms outside Cassero, the main LGBT Center of the city. It is surrounded by Cavaticcio Park, a nice place to chill out, especially in the summer.

name: La Place Cafè
comment: You have to be a paying customer to access to this bathroom, but it is very clean and in perfect condition.

name: Giannis pizza
comment: You have to be a “paying customer”

name: 40 South St, Orlando, FL 32819, USA
directions: In between Mels diner and the transformers photo area

name: Tennispalatsi, 00100 Helsinki, Finland
directions: second floor, right after the stairs from the snack store to upstairs
comment: you do need a WC code but if you’re not going to buy a movie ticket then you can just linger by the door and swoop in when someone else opens it.

name: Cycles for Change Minneapolis
directions: Go through bike shop and turn right before Open Shop area. Go thru door, bear right thru kitchenette and thru glass door. Turn right and there are 2 restrooms on right past drinking fountain. There is also a breat feeding, meditation, prayer room to the left of the kitchenette sink
comment: Bike shop is queer-welcoming and staff are usually happy to help you find restroom. If you need a mobility device accessible restroom you will have to enter via the middle door of the 2010 building (it is the only one with ramp). In that case, the restrooms will be on the left just past the elevator.

name: Club XYZ
comment: I've never had a negative experience here.

name: Salon Lofts
directions: In the front door and on the left, there are two unisex singles.
comment: Every stylist has their own suite, so you can easily slip in and out without anyone noticing.

name: Taziki's Mediterranean Cafe
directions: In the back left corner, the restrooms are on the right side, first the women's (Goddesses), then the men's (Gods).

name: World's Fair Park
directions: On ground lever, next to Clinch street bridge.
comment: Patroled by City officers. I've not had a problem.

name: John Hodges Library
directions: Family restroom located behind Starbucks, gendered restrooms in lobby
comment: Avoid the gendered restrooms, because there was quite a political ordeal about the bathrooms on the campus. They will tolerate transgender people using the unisex.

name: Knoxville City-County Building
directions: Must walk through security check point. Bath rooms are on the M floor in the lobby.
comment: If you are dressed appropriately for business at the courthouse they are very tolerant, but don't dawdle.

name: Kenjo Market
directions: In back, must ask for key.
comment: During late hours, the clerk made me use the disgusting men's room that couldn't have been cleaned in over a week.

name: Barns and Noble
directions: In rear of building, middle section.
comment: Friendly patrons

name: Target
comment: Target has a corporate policy of being trans-friendly, both with the restroom and the fitting rooms. Happy Shopping!

name: The Oliver Hotel
directions: Bathroom in the back that is shared with Tupelo Cafe. Conveniently next to the Speakeasy bar.
comment: Can be crowded at times, but the patrons and staff are trans-friendly.

name: West Town Mall
directions: There are bathrooms in all department stores near the exterior entrances, and There is also a public restroom in the middle of the complex in the food court with a lockable family restroom.
comment: I shop here all the time, and I recommend The department store bathrooms. The staff and patrons are usually very tolerant, even friendly. I would avoid the food court bathroom though.

name: Jackson Homestead/Historic Newton
directions: Museum front door enters from parking lot -- turn right at the desk.
comment: Public building, open to all. If challenged, ask for the assistant to the director, who is an ally. Another gender-neutral restroom exists at the basement level (no changing table).

name: Durant-Kenrick House and Grounds/Historic Newton
directions: Museum door entrance from parking lot -- turn right at the desk.
comment: Open to all. If challenged, ask for the house manager, who is an ally.

name: Kale me crazy
directions: To the left as you walk in
comment: Sign says for customers only

name: Empire Coffee + Pastry
directions: It’s not really a changing table but there’s a bench where you can change a diaper etc. The front of the place has open garage doors but the front door is to the left and it’s right in front of you to the left of two white retro chairs with plants. There’s also tampons in there too. The business is owned by two cis women sisters. The one sister is really nice and was trans friendly. There is a toilet and a urinal and a hook for your belongings. The lock is a simple push button.
comment: I’m assuming that you have to buy something to use it but I mean if it’s busy you can probably get away with it. There is an audible ding if someone opens the door so they’d know about that but the counter would have to pay close attention but otherwise it’s great!

name: Sellers Underground
directions: Past the stage and Pac-Man game down the hall.

name: Minden Hbf (central station)
directions: Next to platform 11 (follow the signs to find the platform)
comment: There are two gender-neutral single-stall toilets. It costs a small fee to enter but you get a voucher which you can use for the bakery or the press shop.

name: Shellharbour Private Hosp, 19-35 Captain Cook Dr, Barrack Heights NSW 2528, Australia
directions: The Medical Imaging Building

name: The Backlot
directions: One on main floor across from the bar, one on upper floor just past the bar
comment: It's a relatively trans-friendly gay bar, so 18+. The lower floor is theoretically accessible, but there isn't much room so movement with mobility devices can be difficult or impossible.
